' Sequence Diagram 02 — Admissible equivocation slash flow.
'
' End-to-end: Validator A signs two distinct blocks at the same seq number,
' both pulled in as dependencies of a third block. The detector emits
' AdmissibleEquivocation; an EquivocationRecord is created; the next
' proposer P attaches a SlashDeploy; the PoS Rholang contract zeros A's
' bond and transfers the forfeited stake to the Coop vault; fork choice
' filters A's latest message out.
'
' Source of truth for Figure 4.1 in docs/theory/slashing/slashing-specification.md.
'
' Color palette (consistent across all sequence diagrams 02, 03, 04, 05, 09):
'   #C62828 red     — adversarial action; buggy/regression write
'   #E65100 orange  — non-trivial detection verdict; slash state mutation
'   #2E7D32 green   — successful honest write; "Valid" verdict
'   #1565C0 blue    — read query (lookup, snapshot)
'   #6A1B9A purple  — Rholang / system-deploy invocation
'   #00838F teal    — inter-validator block gossip
'   #546E7A gray    — internal computation (no side effect)
'
' Render:
'   plantuml -tsvg docs/theory/slashing/diagrams/02-seq-admissible-equivocation.puml

@startuml 02-seq-admissible-equivocation
!theme plain

title Admissible equivocation slash flow

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor              #444444
  LifeLineBorderColor     #666666
  ParticipantBorderColor  #333333
  NoteBorderColor         #666666
  NoteBackgroundColor     #FFF8E1
  GroupBorderColor        #333333
  GroupHeaderFontColor    #222222
  DividerBackgroundColor  #ECEFF1
}
skinparam defaultFontName "sans-serif"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

autonumber

actor       "Equivocator A"      as A   #F8C3B8
actor       "Honest Proposer P"  as P   #C8E6C9
participant "Validate"           as V   #FFECB3
participant "EquivocationDetector" as D #FFECB3
participant "MultiParentCasperImpl" as C #FFECB3
participant "BlockDagStorage"    as DS  #C8E6C9
participant "EquivocationTrackerStore" as T #C8E6C9
participant "CasperSnapshot\n(in-memory snapshot of\nDAG + on-chain state\npre-loaded by block_processor)" as CS #C8E6C9
participant "BlockCreator"       as BC  #B2DFDB
participant "PoS Rholang"        as PoS #D1C4E9
database    "Bond map\n(on-chain state)" as B   #D1C4E9
database    "Coop vault\n(Rholang contract)" as CV  #BBDEFB
participant "ForkChoice"         as FC  #BBDEFB

note over A, FC #ECEFF1
  **Preconditions**
  • Validator A is bonded with stake s > 0 in [Bond map].
  • A's previous block is at sequence number seqN − 1 (creator-justification).
  • Both b1 and b1' will be signed at seqN, where seqN ≥ 1.
  • The "base sequence number" used as the EquivocationRecord key is **seqN − 1**.
  • Every block goes through Validate → EquivocationDetector → MultiParentCasperImpl
    on receipt; the diagram shows D explicitly when its verdict is non-trivial.

  **Color legend**
  red = adversarial / regression  ·  orange = detection verdict / slash effect
  green = honest write / Valid    ·  blue = read query
  purple = Rholang invocation     ·  teal = block gossip   ·  gray = internal
end note

== Phase 1 — First block: A signs honestly ==
A -[#C62828]> V ++ : signed block b1 @ seqN
V -[#1565C0]> D ++ : check_equivocations(b1,\n  requested_as_dependency = ⊥, snapshot)
D -[#546E7A]> D   : extract creator_justification\nfrom b1 (proto_util)
D -[#1565C0]> DS  : latest_message_hash(b1.sender)
note right of D
  Only one signed block by A at seqN
  exists so far → creator_justification
  matches latest_message → no equivocation.
end note
D -[#2E7D32]-> V -- : ValidBlock
V -[#2E7D32]> C ++ : ValidBlock
C -[#2E7D32]> DS  : insert(b1, invalid = false)
deactivate V
deactivate C

== Phase 2 — Second block by A at the SAME seq number ==
A -[#C62828]> V ++ : signed block b1' @ seqN  (b1' ≠ b1)
note over V
  requested_as_dependency = ⊤ is computed
  upstream by the block-processor (not by D);
  it is passed in as a parameter.
end note
V -[#1565C0]> D ++ : check_equivocations(b1',\n  requested_as_dependency = ⊤, snapshot)
D -[#546E7A]> D   : extract creator_justification\nfrom b1' (proto_util)
D -[#1565C0]> DS  : latest_message_hash(b1'.sender)\n→ hash(b1) (already in DAG)
D -[#546E7A]> D   : creator_justification(b1') ≠ b1.hash\n→ equivocation detected
D -[#E65100]-> V -- : InvalidBlock::AdmissibleEquivocation
V -[#E65100]> C ++ : InvalidBlock::AdmissibleEquivocation
deactivate V
note right of C
  AdmissibleEquivocation = the offender
  is **needed** (b1' is in some block's
  justifications). Compare with
  Diagram 03 (Ignorable = unsolicited).
end note

== Phase 3 — Record creation and DAG marking ==
C -[#1565C0]> T   : equivocation_records()
T -[#1565C0]-> C  : current set (empty for (A, seqN−1))
note over C, T #FFCDD2
  ⚠ Pre-fix Rust regression: this RMW is lock-free.
  Two threads can both observe "absent" and both
  insert. Bug fix #2 (T-9.2) re-locks via
  access_equivocations_tracker. See Diagram 09.
end note
C -[#E65100]> T   : insert_equivocation_record(A, seqN − 1, ∅)
C -[#E65100]> DS  : insert(b1', invalid = true)
deactivate C

== Phase 4 — Honest proposer P begins next block ==
P -[#00838F]> BC ++ : propose new block at seqM\n(seqM > seqN, P scheduled by\nleader-election or proposer thread)
note over BC
  prepare_slashing_deploys reads from a
  CasperSnapshot pre-loaded by the
  block-processor — NOT live DS calls.
end note
BC -[#1565C0]> CS  : casper_snapshot.dag.invalid_latest_messages()
CS -[#1565C0]-> BC : { (A, b1') }
BC -[#1565C0]> T   : equivocation_records()
T -[#1565C0]-> BC  : { (A, seqN − 1, ∅) }
BC -[#1565C0]> CS  : casper_snapshot.on_chain_state.bonds_map
CS -[#1565C0]-> BC : bonds_map
BC -[#546E7A]> BC  : filter offenders where\nbonds_map[offender] > 0\n→ keep A
note right of BC
  prepare_slashing_deploys
  (block_creator.rs:287-332).
  Skipped here if proposer
  itself is unbonded (fix #8).
end note
create SD
BC -[#6A1B9A]> SD  : new SlashDeploy(b1', P.pubkey,\n  generateSlashDeployRandomSeed(P, seqM))\n(struct lives in bP.body.system_deploys)
BC -[#546E7A]> BC  : assemble candidate block bP\nincluding SlashDeploy as a system deploy

== Phase 5 — Local evaluation: SlashDeploy fires in PoS ==
note over BC, FC #ECEFF1
  Block deploys are evaluated locally during proposal
  to compute the post-state. Other validators replay
  the same evaluation when they receive the gossiped block.
end note
SD -[#6A1B9A]> PoS ++ : @PoS!("slash", deployerId,\n            blockHash = b1'.hash,\n            sysAuthToken, returnCh)\n(parameter names match PoS.rhox:435)
PoS -[#546E7A]> PoS  : sysAuthTokenOps.check(sysAuthToken)\n→ TRUE (system deploy)
PoS -[#1565C0]> PoS  : invalidBlocks.get(b1'.hash) → A
PoS -[#1565C0]> B    : valBond ← state.allBonds[A]
B   -[#1565C0]-> PoS : valBond
PoS -[#6A1B9A]> CV   : @posVault!("transfer",\n  coopMultiVaultAddr, valBond,\n  posAuthKey, transferDoneCh)
CV  -[#2E7D32]-> PoS : transferDone (success)
PoS -[#E65100]> B    : atomic stateUpdateCh!{\n  allBonds := allBonds[A := 0],\n  activeValidators := \\ {A},\n  committedRewards := \\ {A}\n} ; (true, Nil)\n(single map-construction step,\n PoS.rhox:473-482)
PoS -[#2E7D32]-> SD -- : (true, Nil) on returnCh\nvia runMVar
deactivate BC

== Phase 6 — Block bP gossiped; fork choice updates ==
BC -[#00838F]> P    : finalized block bP (post-state hash)\nincluding the executed SlashDeploy.\nP gossips bP to the network; other\nvalidators replay the deploys to verify\nthe post-state.
note right of FC
  ForkChoice does not receive a push.
  On every fork-choice computation it
  reads on-chain bonds_map and **filters**
  validators with bond = 0 from latest-
  message consideration.
end note
FC -[#1565C0]> B    : on_chain_state.bonds_map
B  -[#1565C0]-> FC  : bonds_map (with allBonds[A] = 0)
FC -[#E65100]> FC   : filter A's latest_message\nfrom GHOST estimator
deactivate P

@enduml
